<subSubSection id="C379979F162B3669AE76FD09DB063044" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDCC414162B3669AE76FD09DB063044" blockId="16.[869,1493,698,851]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B9171806162B3669AE76FD09DDE831C4" bold="true" box="[869,1005,698,723]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is patronymic, named for Professor Cleide Costa (MZUSP) on the occasion of her 80 
<superScript id="7C16695C162B3669AEBDFD4ADDB9301F" attach="left" box="[942,956,761,776]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">th</superScript>
birthday, in honour of her contributions to the systematics of 
<taxonomicName id="4C63BF97162B3669A914FCA9DA873024" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1031,1154,794,819]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
and pioneering studies on immature stages of Neotropical beetles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
